Maritsa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next Olympic swimmer\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 468}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, they will be standing right next to Maritza McClendon, not only was she the guest instructor at the free national event co-sponsored by the U.S. swimming, she's a decorated Olympian and a history maker.\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 538, \"end\": 545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maritsa\", \"score\": 0.9317264576154206, \"rank\": 0.0732763804510221, \"text\": \"Maritza\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maritsa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maritsa\"}, {\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999998458445253, \"rank\": 1.528355766385485e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the guest instructor\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 594}, {\"ngram\": \"the free national event\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 621}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. swimming\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"a history maker\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She's the first black woman to make it on the nation's Olympic swim team took home sliver in Athens back in 2004.\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 799, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9189818709052104, \"rank\": 0.08816072306323407, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first black woman\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 733}, {\"ngram\": \"the nation's Olympic swim team\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"home sliver\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For her, it's not just a profession, it's personal.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 872, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just a profession\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you do not know, 64 percent of African-American children do not know how to swim; and 45 percent of Hispanic children do not know how to swim,\\\" explained McClendon.\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 1042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 909, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"score\": 0.9999990630962953, \"rank\": 9.367181973046332e-07, \"text\": \"African-American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans\", \"score\": 0.8004853782987646, \"rank\": 0.24924205626307136, \"text\": \"Hispanic\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"64 percent\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"45 percent\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"McClendon\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1041}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So, it's really important to introduce them to the education as to why we do water safety.\\\"\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1135, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the education\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1104}, {\"ngram\": \"water safety\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a lesson, Yocelyn Melendez wants for her kids.\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lesson\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1150}, {\"ngram\": \"Yocelyn Melendez\", \"from\": 1152, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"her kids\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1187}]}, 